# Base UI library: Material UI (mui)

## Package import
Always import from `test-client-design-system` — NEVER from the underlying library directly:
```tsx
import { Button, vars } from 'test-client-design-system';
import 'test-client-design-system/src/design-tokens/tokens.css';
```

## Design Token Rules
- NEVER hardcode hex colors — use CSS variables or `vars` references
- NEVER hardcode font sizes or spacing values
- TypeScript access: `import { designTokens, vars } from 'test-client-design-system'`

## vars.* shape (typed CSS-variable references)
- vars.color           — brand500, actionPrimary, actionSecondary, success500, warning500, danger500, background, surface, textMain, textMuted, borderDivider
- vars.colorToken      — greyPage, greyPageLight, greyButtonsBg, greyTextField, greyStroke, greyDrawerHandle, greyTextIcons, greyLightGrey, orangeOrangeWarning, turquoiseTurquoise, greySecondaryBodyText, whiteWhite … (52 total)
- vars.radius          — small, medium, large, round
- vars.radiusToken     — radiusXXS, radiusXS, radiusS, radiusM, radiusL, radiusXL, radiusFull, radius10 … (10)
- vars.font            — labelSml, headlineMed18Med, headlineMedHeadlineReg16Reg, headlineMedHeadlineReg16Med, headlineMedHeadlineRegLabelLarge14Med, labelReg14Reg, lableSami12, typographyInter16 (each: .family .size .weight .lineHeight)
- vars.spacing         — spaceXXS, spaceXS, spaceS, spaceM, spaceL, spaceXL, spaceXXL, spaceXXXL, space10, space48, space166, space156, space5, space45, space30, space665, space25, space29, space1088, space1249, space27, space15, space9, space26, space13
- vars.size            — borderWidthXXS, borderWidthXS, borderWidthS, borderWidthM, borderWidthL, opacityHover, opacityFocus, opacityPressed
- vars.shadow          — small, medium, large, inner
- vars.gradient        — mILogoGradient, brandGradient, brandPurple, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom, gradientsCustom

Usage example:
```tsx
import { vars } from 'test-client-design-system';
<Box sx={{ backgroundColor: vars.color.actionPrimary, borderRadius: vars.radius.medium }} />
```

## Namespace Component API
All Figma-derived components are exported as namespace objects.
Import and use them like this:
```tsx
import { Tasks } from 'test-client-design-system';

<Tasks.DashboardContent onClick={fn} isLoading={false} />
```

### Standard props (every AI-generated component accepts these)
- `onClick?: () => void` — click handler
- `onHover?: () => void` — mouse-enter handler
- `isDisabled?: boolean` — disables the component
- `isLoading?: boolean` — shows a spinner; disables interaction
- `children?: React.ReactNode` — content slot
- `sx?: Record<string, unknown>` — style overrides (spread last; developer wins)
- `className?: string` — class overrides

